    "answer": "You can run this project locally in two ways:\n\n1.  **Manual run:**\n    *   Start the API in one terminal using:\n        ```powershell\n        uvicorn app.api.main:app --host 0.0.0.0 --port 8000\n        ```\n    *   Start the UI in a second terminal using:\n        ```powershell\n        streamlit run app/ui/home.py\n        ```\n    *   Useful local URLs will be:\n        *   API docs: `http://127.0.0.1:8000/docs`\n        *   API health: `http://127.0.0.1:8000/health`\n        *   UI: `http://127.0.0.1:8501`\n\n2.  **Local container run with Docker:**\n    *   Use the command:\n        ```powershell\n        docker compose up --build\n        ```\n    *   This will start the API on port `8000` and the Streamlit UI on port `8501`.",
